ratings.question_text: Overall, how would you rate the workload of this course in comparison to other Yale courses you have taken?
What is your overall assessment of this course?
Do you expect to use this class for credit toward your major, or toward a pre-professional program?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 111 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 111 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: This is an independent project, so it really just depends on your own motivation and your advisor.

Required for the major so not much choice in terms of whether or not we can take the course. Bill Summers is incredibly unresponsive and his lack of support was my primary frustration of this project. Your experience is really shaped by your adviser and how they guide (or don't) guide you, so think about this earlier.
